-- Czech Stocks: Erste Bank, Komercni, Telefonica Czech Active
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-02-14T16:15:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-14/czech-stocks-erste-bank-komercni-telefonica-czech-active.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
fell 0.6 percent to 1,004.7 at its 4:28 p.m. close in Prague,
after rising 2 percent yesterday.  The following were among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)  , a unit of Societe Generale SA,
slid 0.8 percent to 3,680 koruna and Austria’s  Erste Group Bank
AG (RBAG)   dropped 3.1 percent to 460.3 koruna. Moody’s
Investors Service cut its debt ratings on six euro-area nations
and said it may downgrade the U.K., France and Austria.  Telefonica Czech Republic AS (SPTT)   closed unchanged at
376 koruna, after earlier rising as much as 1 percent. The phone
company was raised to “hold” from “sell” at KBC Securities.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
